<h1>About Massar Networking</h1>

<div class="rightpic"><img alt="Jeroen Massar at Internetdagarna 2008" title="Jeroen Massar at Internetdagarna 2008" src="http://jeroen.massar.ch/gfx/jeroen_massar_dagarna.jpg" /><br />Jeroen presenting at Internetdagarna 2008</div>

<h2>Goals</h2>
<p>
Massar Networking is a specialized Internet research company dedicated to making the Internet a better place.
</p>

<p>
We provide tailored, high performance, scalable and secure solutions in the area of network accounting, performance profiling, routing, security and anonymity.
</p>

<h2>Structure</h2>

<p>
Massar Networking is a <span title="In German: Einzelunternehmen">Swiss sole proprietorship</span> run by <a href="http://jeroen.massar.ch">Jeroen Massar</a>.
</p>

<p>
We operate out of Z&uuml;rich, Switzerland from where we have excellent network connectivity, a perfectly healthy legal climate and excellent airport connections to Europe and the rest of the world.
</p>

<h2>Staff</h2>
<p>
Jeroen Massar is an experienced network researcher who designed and implemented large parts of the <a href="http://www.sixxs.net">SixXS</a> project.
The work he did on SixXS includes amongst others the Tunnel broker system itself, the PoP software <a href="http://www.sixxs.net/faq/sixxs/?faq=sixxsd">sixxsd</a> and the
<a href="http://www.sixxs.net/tools/ayiya/">AYIYA</a>, <a href="http://www.sixxs.net/tools/heartbeat/">heartbeat</a> and <a href="http://www.sixxs.net/tools/tic/">TIC</a> protocols.
</p>

<p>
For <a href="http://www.zurich.ibm.com">IBM Research</a> he designed and implemented the high performance <a href="http://www.zurich.ibm.com/aurora/">AURORA Network Performance Profiling</a>
system which analyzes NetFlow, IPFIX and sFlow.
</p>

<p>
He also designed and implemented the <a href="http://www.sixxs.net/tools/grh/">Ghost Route Hunter (GRH)</a>, an IPv6 BGP routing monitoring
system and provided IPv6 patches to existing software to make them IPv6 capable, amongst others
<a href="http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/wishlist/ipv6-build.html">PuTTY</a>,
<a href="https://lists.torproject.org/pipermail/tor-dev/2011-December/003113.html">Tor</a> and
<a href="http://www.fping.com/">fping</a>.
</p>

